#BASIC LEVEL SQL PROBLEMS 

-- PROBLEM STATEMENT 1
write a SQL query that Will return all the opposites of the values in the Value column. If a number is negative, make it positive and vice versa. 
For this problem statement, your database table is structured like this: 

'CREATE TABLE 'Book' ('id' INTEGER,'Value' INTEGER);
INSERT INTO Book (id,Value) VALUES(1,-56),
INSERT INTO Book (id,Value) VALUES (2,76),
INSERT INTO Book (id,Value) VALUES (3,-84),
INSERT INTO Book (id,Value) VALUES (4,96),
INSERT INTO Book (id,Value) VALUES (5,-47);'

AND Hereâ€™s what your query should return:

56, -76, 84, -96, 47

